    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3f313ec5_b5ea7541",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/base/Result.h",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 153,
      "author": {
        "id": 1233742
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-08-21T20:42:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "After some changes I made, I think we specifically don\u0027t want to ref-returning versions.  As part of the changes to make sure we can propagate move-only types, I made it so that unwrap() and unwrapErr() moves the value out of the Result, making it invalid.  This is what Rust does too, but it has stronger compiler guarantees preventing the Result from being used again.\n\nSo instead of returning a ref, we should always move the value out in this case.",
      "parentUuid": "7a1c9e71_a8dd8102",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 149,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 153,
        "endChar": 5
      },
      "revId": "13a472292d1910844c812092940821fc2913b1d0",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4e36a808_9d593aa6",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/base/Result.h",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 159,
      "author": {
        "id": 1080076
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-08-20T21:25:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "these functions always return a copy, so there won\u0027t be a way to return some big object (string/vector) and move it out of the Result\u003c\u003e. Should these return references instead?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 149,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 159,
        "endChar": 5
      },
      "revId": "13a472292d1910844c812092940821fc2913b1d0",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
    },
